description:
&lt;p&gt;Calling all General Medicine Doctors!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you interested in picking up extra shifts but fancy a change of scenery or a new challenge?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here at Yeovil District Hospital, a small Acute Trust with a welcoming community feel, we are looking to increase our Locum Bank services within our General Medicine department, specifially with our Trust Fellows and Specialty Doctors, we have opportunities for you to expand your skills and knowledge through our Locum shifts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Caring for 200,000 local people when they need it most, last year Yeovil Hospital helped deliver 1,463 babies, carried out 122,271 Radiology tests, and much more! Our A&amp;E team is consistently meeting the four hour waiting time targets and we are one of the few Hospitals nationally to have 0% nursing vacancies, due to our exceptional recruitment initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Why join Yeovil District Hospital&#39;s Locum Bank you ask?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are a number of perks if you join our Locum Bank such as;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The allowed flexibility of working hours that fit in with your personal circumstances.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We will ensure that you have priority over Agency staff when it comes to filling our shifts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to training courses if you pick up shifts regularly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive rates of pay.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A dedicated Rota Team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On site car parking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So what are you waiting for?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To express an interest or find out more information on joining our Locum Bank and the processes involved, please contact the Medical Recruitment Team on the below contact details.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Email:&lt;/strong&gt; Medical.Recruitment@ydh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Telephone:&lt;/strong&gt; 01935 384616&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that applicants must be GMC registered in order to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
